[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing resource loading issues**\n\nIt looks like our ClassLoader returns null for all resources, which is causing System.loadLibrary to attempt loading a nonexistent library and throw an exception. I think we could catch that UnsatisfiedLinkError. For line 162, that should be enough. For line 157, maybe we should test if `DefaultResourceLoader` returns an invalid URL, ensuring the URL isn't null before it falls to System.loadLibrary. But line 157 is covered even if it is null, so I need to avoid using System.loadLibrary if possible.\n\n**Exploring JavaCompiler options**\n\nI'm thinking about whether I could run a custom in-memory copy of NativeLibraryLoader with JavaCompiler. Wait, though — wouldn’t coverage be tied to the original class? That seems off. I wonder if I could use Unsafe to mutate static final OSNAME and figure out if that could be a viable solution. But maybe mapping it might not work as planned either. I’ll need to navigate these options carefully!\n\n**Evaluating class initialization**\n\nI’m considering the need for an invalid class initialization. The `NativeLibraryLoader` is making static calls to `tmpdir` using `os.name`. Since we're on Mac, the `isWindows` flag is false, which seems fine. But I’m thinking: if I set `os.name` to Mac, will it affect `System.loadLibrary`? I don't think so. It’s important to preserve the original property for the rest of the process.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_002b0d3570c69a040169f0cd8f14ec819cbcf2b5b9fdf1923a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8M2wIqwxjsw4N8gIuRscRW7snxAV0wiGU8KFlG6shU4xbpZxBgra3JsaTymcA5-jMqACXvJnigbyxnrEtU6p1icrvGcvNu86L2FOXVpBgNMwX-q4RDIEJUNSNMJ1hwSPBGRDB2iZscd-KjEafDHSEr763E-nt_6PWBdBTRtVWcpNLHEHmIngaOemH3Cp2d96yLNC2DB7ii_1EjcZJGqV3P1yRho3y6Qk8Wo4CiVTPI7Y0qCOKV534QTd-CpEzujtZaQSebX4Lj6BA1CH60S0HhNlMaVVrJaYpa5jLWNyuGWD8KDdLQCGUBjTlVwb2f6wkVjpzM-17z3T2A