stem.loadLibrary to attempt loading a nonexistent library and throw an exception. I think we could catch that UnsatisfiedLinkError. For line 162, that should be enough. For line 157, maybe we should test if `DefaultResourceLoader` returns an invalid URL, ensuring the URL isn't null before it falls to System.loadLibrary. But line 157 is covered even if it is null, so I need to avoid using System.loadLibrary if possible.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring JavaCompiler options**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether I could run a custom in-memory copy of NativeLibraryLoader with JavaCompiler. Wait, though — wouldn’t coverage be tied to the original class? That seems off. I wonder if I could use Unsafe to mutate static final OSNAME and figure out if that could be a viable solution. But maybe mapping it might not work as planned either. I’ll need to navigate these options carefully!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class initialization**\\n\\nI’m considering the need for an invalid class initialization. The `NativeLibraryLoader` is making static calls to `tmpdir` using `os.name`. Since we're on Mac, the `isWindows` flag is false, which seems fine. But I’m thinking: if I set `os.name` to Mac, will it affect `System.loadLibrary`? I don't think so. It’s important to preserve the original property for the rest of the process.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_3q1xDZ3OhkmxHs7uXehTHrXY|fc_002b0d3570c69a040169f0cdb08644819c9fa67217e78bec39", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.netty/netty-all/4.0.23.Final/src/test/java/io_netty/netty_all/NativeLibraryLoaderTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_netty.netty_all;\n\nimport io.netty.util.internal.NativeLibraryLoader;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.AfterAll;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\n\npublic class NativeLibraryLoaderTest {\n    private static final String LIBRARY_NAME = \"netty_resource_probe\";\n    private static final String ORIGINAL_OS_NAME = System.getProperty(\"os.name\");\n\n    static {\n        System.setProperty(\"os.name\", \"Mac OS X\");\n    }\n\n    @AfterAll\n    static void restoreOsName() {\n        if (ORIGINAL_OS_NAME == null) {\n            System.clearProperty(\"os.name\");\n        } else {\n            System.setProperty(\"os.name\", ORIGINAL_OS_NAME);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void loadSearchesForPackagedNativeLibraryResourcesBeforeFallingBackToSystemLoader() {\n        RecordingClassLoader loader = new RecordingClassLoader();\n\n        UnsatisfiedLinkError error = Assertions.assertThrows(\n                UnsatisfiedLinkError.class,\n                () -> NativeLibraryLoader.load(LIBRARY_NAME, loader));\n\n        String mappedLibraryResource = \"META-INF/native/\" + System.mapLibraryName(LIBRARY_NAME);\n        String macFallbackResource = macFallbackResource(mappedLibraryResource);\n\n        Assertions.assertTrue(loader.resourceNames().contains(mappedLibraryResource));\n        Assertions.assertTrue(loader.resourceNames().contains(macFallbackResource));\n        Assertions.assertTrue(error.getMessage().contains(LIBRARY_NAME));\n    }\n\n    private static String macFallbackResource(String mappedLibraryResource) {\n        if (mappedLibraryResource.endsWith(\".jnilib\")) {\n            return \"META-INF/native/lib\" + LIBRARY_NAME + \".dynlib\";\n        }\n        return \"META-INF/native/lib\" + LIBRARY_NAME + \".jnilib\";\n    }\n\n    private static final class RecordingClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private final List<String> resourceNames = new ArrayList<String>();\n\n        private RecordingClassLoader() {\n            super(NativeLibraryLoaderTest.class.getClassLoader());\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public URL getResource(String name) {\n            resourceNames.add(name);\n            return null;\n        }\n\n        private List<String> resourceNames() {\n            return resourceNames;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 255, "output": 2863, "cacheRead": 31744, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34862, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777388941823, "responseId": "resp_002b0d3570c69a040169f0cd8e4f00819c9abdc70a7d390077"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_3q1xDZ3OhkmxHs7uXehTHrXY|fc_002b0d3570c69a040169f0cdb08644819c9fa67217e78bec39", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 2533 bytes to tests/src/io.netty/netty-all/4.0.23.Final/src/test/java/io_netty/netty_all/NativeLibraryLoaderTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777388978720}]}
