[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering creating a test using the classloader to return a valid URL for a fallback resource. This way, I can avoid using `System.loadLibrary` and manage the line that follows. However, when `System.load(tmpFile)` runs, it could try using an invalid file and throw an error. If I use a real temporary file, it triggers the file copy code, which may not be ideal. The assertion order could come after NativeLibraryLoader.load, checking for potential `UnsatisfiedLinkError`.
