\\n\\nI’m considering enhancing the current test by selecting a \\\"jnilib-mapped\\\" name specifically for platforms that support it, otherwise asserting that the fallback for the jnilib branch isn't available for that JDK. But it seems that’s not the best route.\\n\\nInstead, maybe I could introduce a custom test resource for `META-INF/native/libnetty_resource_probe.jnilib` and utilize Java's `System.loadLibrary` as a fallback. That might provide a better way to handle the situation!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering library names**\\n\\nI'm pondering whether `System.mapLibraryName` on Linux returns `.so`, and I wonder if the function behaves differently for names that start with \\\"lib\\\" and end with \\\".jnilib.\\\" It seems like it's worth testing both cases to see what we get. If there's any distinction in output, that could be essential information. Let’s dive into testing this further to clarify how the function handles different library extensions!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_I2J9xhY8Ui83hrQAiXxEnbS9|fc_002b0d3570c69a040169f0ce76b224819c8596cacca50310cc", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "jshell <<'EOF'\nString[] names={\"libfoo.jnilib\",\"/tmp/libfoo.jnilib\",\"META-INF/native/libfoo.jnilib\",\"foo.so\",\"libfoo.so\"};\nfor(String n:names) System.out.println(n+\" -> \"+System.mapLibraryName(n));\nEOF", "timeout": 20}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2594, "output": 882, "cacheRead": 39424, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42900, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777389137857, "responseId": "resp_002b0d3570c69a040169f0ce52f090819cb3d77bc9eae781a3"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_I2J9xhY8Ui83hrQAiXxEnbS9|fc_002b0d3570c69a040169f0ce76b224819c8596cacca50310cc", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "|  Welcome to JShell -- Version 25.0.2\n|  For an introduction type: /help intro\n\njshell> names ==> String[5] { \"libfoo.jnilib\", \"/tmp/libfoo.jnilib\" ... \", \"foo.so\", \"libfoo.so\" }\n\njshell> libfoo.jnilib -> liblibfoo.jnilib.so\n/tmp/libfoo.jnilib -> lib/tmp/libfoo.jnilib.so\nMETA-INF/native/libfoo.jnilib -> libMETA-INF/native/libfoo.jnilib.so\nfoo.so -> libfoo.so.so\nlibfoo.so -> liblibfoo.so.so\n\njshell> "}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777389180099}]}
